Description: 2004 Fender Custom Shop 1960 Relic Stratocaster Aged. DESCRIPTION What makes this guitar special: A killer sounding '60 Relic with a super cool vibe & exquisite playability. The vintage white finish looks fantastic & really authentic. The slender profile neck is a dream to play & is very comfortable. But the real magic lies in the trio of staggered pole single coils that deliver clear, bell-like tones that ring for days. Professionally inspected & set up by the experts at Cream City Music, so it's ready for action upon arrival. Cosmetic Condition: Purposely "aged" at the factory to give it that well-played vintage look. Excellent Condition. Neck: Nicely rounded, C-shape maple neck with beautifully figured rosewood fingerboard & cream dot inlays. Frets are in great shape with only a tiny bit of wear & tons of life in them. Vintage-style nickel tuners are in perfect working condition. 1 5/8" nut width; 25 1/2" scale length. Neck is straight & truss rod works fine. Body: Contoured, solid alder body finished in a vintage white. Vintage-style tremolo bridge with adjustable saddles & original trem arm. 3-ply mint pickguard & single-ply trem cover. Guitar weighs 8 lbs 0.8 oz. Electronics: Fender Custom Shop single coils with staggered poles. Bridge - 5.69K ohms; Middle - 5.71K ohms; Neck - 5.68K ohms. Master volume & dual tone controls with 5-way selector switch. All electronics are in perfect working condition. Case: Brown tolex hardshell case included along with COA & some accessories.
Title: Fender Custom Shop '60 Relic Stratocaster Aged White. 2004
